---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Product Managers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Product Managers working internationally, covering PM positions abroad, tech product careers, and global product development opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Product Managers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Product Managers working abroad, building products internationally, and pursuing careers across tech companies, startups, and enterprises worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/product-manager-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/product-manager-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Product Manager Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Product Managers define product strategy, prioritize features, and guide development teams to build successful products. International PM careers offer opportunities to work on global products, experience different market dynamics, and build products for diverse user bases.
      </p>
      <p>
        International product management opportunities exist through global tech companies, international startups, enterprises expanding digital products worldwide, and the inherently global nature of software products serving users across borders.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Product Managers working abroad across tech companies, startups, and enterprises worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Product Managers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'High-pressure role', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Stakeholder and user research travel', typical: 'Often provided' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Meeting and desk work', typical: 'Consider for profession' },
          { need: 'Stress management', why: 'Deadline and stakeholder pressure', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Wellness programs', why: 'Demanding lifestyle', typical: 'Often at tech companies' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Tech Company Benefits</h3>
      <p>
        Product managers typically work at tech companies or digital enterprises that offer comprehensive benefits. Major tech employers provide premium coverage including mental health support, wellness programs, and generous preventive care. Startup benefits vary but often include competitive health coverage.
      </p>
      <p>
        International PM roles at established companies usually include relocation support and benefits continuation. The competitive talent market for product managers drives strong benefits packages.
      </p>

      <h3>Role Intensity</h3>
      <p>
        Product management is demanding—balancing stakeholder expectations, engineering constraints, user needs, and business goals. Mental health support and stress management resources are valuable for sustainable PM careers. The role often involves irregular hours and high accountability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Tech Company</h3>
      <p>
        Major tech employer. Comprehensive benefits. Competitive packages. Tech offers premium coverage.
      </p>

      <h3>Startup</h3>
      <p>
        Growth-stage company. Benefits variable. Equity included. Startups offer opportunity.
      </p>

      <h3>Enterprise</h3>
      <p>
        Large corporation digital team. Corporate benefits. Established structure. Enterprise offers stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Consultancy</h3>
      <p>
        Product consultancy. Firm benefits. Client variety. Consulting offers diversity.
      </p>

      <h3>Scale-up</h3>
      <p>
        Rapid growth company. Improving benefits. Dynamic environment. Scale-ups offer growth.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Product Managers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Product Managers working abroad across tech companies, startups, and enterprises worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare PM Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Product track record. Shipped products. Measurable impact. Experience is primary credential.
      </p>

      <h3>Education</h3>
      <p>
        MBA or technical degree common. Business or CS background. Varied paths. Education helps but not required.
      </p>

      <h3>Certifications</h3>
      <p>
        Product certifications available. Agile credentials. Less emphasized in field. Certifications supplement.
      </p>

      <h3>Domain Knowledge</h3>
      <p>
        Industry expertise. Market understanding. Technical fluency. Domain enables effectiveness.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Stress</h3>
      <p>
        Stakeholder pressure. Deadline intensity. Accountability demands. Mental health support essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Meetings</h3>
      <p>
        Meeting-heavy days. Communication intensive. Decision fatigue. Schedule management important.
      </p>

      <h3>Ergonomic</h3>
      <p>
        Desk and meeting work. Variable environments. Extended sitting. Ergonomic coverage valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Travel</h3>
      <p>
        User research trips. Stakeholder visits. Conference attendance. Travel coverage relevant.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Strategy</h3>
      <p>
        Product vision. Roadmap development. Prioritization. Strategy guides direction.
      </p>

      <h3>Coordination</h3>
      <p>
        Cross-functional alignment. Stakeholder management. Team collaboration. Coordination enables execution.
      </p>

      <h3>Discovery</h3>
      <p>
        User research. Market analysis. Opportunity identification. Discovery informs decisions.
      </p>

      <h3>Delivery</h3>
      <p>
        Feature shipping. Launch management. Iteration cycles. Delivery creates value.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Demand</h3>
      <p>
        PM skills highly sought. Tech expansion worldwide. Competitive compensation. Demand strong.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Senior PM. Group product manager. VP Product. Chief product officer. Clear progression.
      </p>

      <h3>Remote Potential</h3>
      <p>
        Remote PM work growing. Location flexibility increasing. Hybrid common. Remote opportunities expanding.
      </p>

      <h3>Compensation</h3>
      <p>
        Premium salaries typical. Equity common. Competitive market. Compensation attractive.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a product manager considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Tech companies typically provide comprehensive benefits. Verify mental health coverage for demanding role. Relocation packages often included.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do tech companies provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Major tech companies yes. Premium packages common. Relocation support typical. Verify specific offer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health coverage important for PMs?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for role intensity. Stakeholder pressure. Decision fatigue. Mental health support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Can I work remotely internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Increasingly possible. Company policies vary. Some roles require presence. Remote potential growing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about startup coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Variable by stage. Competitive to attract talent. Less comprehensive than big tech. Evaluate carefully.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Strong demand continuing. Digital products expanding. Global opportunities. Outlook excellent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits packages thoroughly. Ensure mental health coverage for role demands. Consider wellness programs for work-life balance. Verify international coverage scope for relocation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Product Managers shape digital experiences worldwide. Your coverage should support PM careers—addressing role intensity, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across product work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your PM Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Product Managers working abroad across tech companies, startups, and enterprises worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
